======================================
Preparing your workstation
======================================

The following packages are needed on Ubuntu (tested using 14.04).
Install using apt-get

arduino
build-essential
gawk
git
minicom
subversion

Your user needs to be a member of the 'dialout' group.
This can be done using "useradd -G dialout <username>"
You must re-login for the group changes to take effect.


======================================
Programming the adapter
======================================

To program the adapter, run the script "program_adapter.sh"


======================================
Building your project
======================================

In the code/Autopilot directory, running "make" will compile your
project.  Running "make upload" will program the compiled code to the
device.

Your changes should be in code/Autopilot/Autopilot.pde and code/libraries/PID/